==English==
===Etymology===
''[[drive]]'' + ''[[-eth]]'', the archaic third-person singular present tense suffix

===Verb form===
'''driveth'''
# {{archaic}} [[third-person singular]] form of ''to [[drive]]''.
#:The Nine Books of the Danish History of Saxo Grammaticus [http://www.gwerin.org.uk/articles/viking_sagas1.htm online] - ''Our son is slain, let us riot in battle; my eager love for him driveth me to my death, that I may not be left outliving my dear child.''